@startuml hand-off-session-architecture

title hand_off_session — module architecture

package "MCP entry" {
  [withMcpGuard\n(deny external)] as Guard
  [hand-off-session\nhandler-main] as Handler
}

package "Session creation" {
  [spawn_session handler] as Spawn
  [adapter createSession\nClaude / Codex] as Adapter
}

package "Resource transfer" {
  [resource-transfer\ncoordinator] as Transfer
  [sessionRepo\ncwd marker] as Sessions
  [agentDeckTeamRepo\nmemberships] as Teams
  [taskRepo\nreassignOwner] as Tasks
}

package "Close caller" {
  [sessionManager.close] as Close
  [closed side effects\nclear marker + leave teams] as SideEffects
}

Guard --> Handler
Handler --> Spawn : prompt + cwd + handOff metadata
Spawn --> Adapter
Adapter --> Sessions : successor session row
Handler --> Transfer
Transfer --> Sessions : move marker
Transfer --> Teams : swapLead / addMember
Transfer --> Tasks : preserve-team task reassignment
Handler --> Close
Close --> SideEffects

note bottom
  Plan files and project archival records are outside this MCP tool.
  External skills or project conventions orchestrate those assets through prompt text.
end note

@enduml
